  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dda\u0dbd\u0da7\u0db8 \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc3\u0dca\u0d87\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A family that eats jackfruit every three meals",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A news was reported today that a sick mother in Bibila Radaliyadda village is living in a hut with three children due to economic difficulties these days.",
        "DM Padmavathy (36) who has lost her husband and lives in a hut in Radaliadda Igiyangoda village, says that she has been living a miserable life for years with her mother and her three school-going children.",
        "She works hard to support her three children by harvesting the crops grown near the lake in the village and selling them to the houses of the village with the daily income of 200-300 rupees.",
        "She is unable to provide even one meal a day to her three children, she says that there were times when she used to feed the children only jackfruit for three meals until she found money again after the kilo of rice she brings home from the sale of fruits.",
        "Padmavathi says that the children going to school do not have enough clothes including school equipment and there is no kerosene to study with bottle lamps at night.",
        "\"My husband is dead. I, along with my three children, have raised a plant in a land given by my mother and live covered with polythene. We don't have any facilities including toilets and water. We get wet in the rain. It is unsafe for adult girls to live in this house.",
        "In order to support the children, I go to the lake and cut grasses including mugununa and sell them to the houses in the village.",
        "Nothing has been received from the government. There is no kerosene to put in the lamps for the children to study at night. Until now, no one has come to hear our sorrow, there is no one to tell us. I am sick and there is no way to get medicine, if there is someone to help my three children study, we will have it,\" she said."
      ],
